o to facilitate peer group interaction and the free exchange of ideas, focusing on the provision of constructive feedback from peer group members and more senior members of the academic community</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The seminar series was the first to address the research questions posed by the transition to IFRS, and attracted participation from leading global academics (Universities of Cambridge, Harvard, Stanford, MIT, Chicago) and Board members of the leading global accounting bodies, including IASB and FASB.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>873F8148-D227-4BB4-B318-2FDCFDBBA98E</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>5460c88c9ed175.98308831</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Financial Services, and Management Consultancy</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>https://research.mbs.ac.uk/investment-risk/Events.aspx</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">RES-451-25-4253</gtr:identifier><gtr:identifier type="RES">RES-451-25-4253</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>5E9AA4EC-49E3-4D6A-B545-79DA07CE39E0</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Management &amp; Business Studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject></gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchTopics><gtr:researchTopic><gtr:id>5E9AA4EC-49E3-4D6A-B545-79DA07CE39E0</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Management &amp; Business Studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchTopic></gtr:researchTopics><gtr:rcukProgrammes/></gtr:project></gtr:projectComposition></gtr:projectOverview>